A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Steve Mensch; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Steve Mensch on December 6, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Steve Mensch was raised in Goshen, New York, where he demonstrated early
5 determination and skill as a member of the Boy Scouts as well as claimed victory in the
6 Pinewood Derby, a celebrated Cub Scouts racing event; and
7 WHEREAS, he cultivated a lifelong passion for tennis and hockey from a young age,
8 continuing to play and excel at both sports well into adulthood, and he had a deep love for
9 scuba diving and the ocean; and
10 WHEREAS, he further pursued his love of aviation, earning his pilot's license on September
11 18, 2020, after completing his second first solo flight at Falcon Field in Fayette County; and
12 WHEREAS, he custom-built an RV-12 two-seat, single-engine plane, incorporating special
13 markings to honor his children and assigning it the tail number 702DP in tribute to his
14 beloved wife, Danila Pirochta Mensch, whom he affectionately called "DP"; and
