15 WHEREAS, he additionally dedicated time to volunteering with the Young Eagles, a
16 nonprofit program that has provided free flights to youth ages 8â€“17 for 30 years, inspiring
17 the next generation of aviation enthusiasts; and
18 WHEREAS, as a pivotal figure in Georgia's film and television industry, he played a vital
19 role in advocating for the tax credits that established the state as a premier destination for
20 film production, significantly contributing to Georgia's economic growth; and
21 WHEREAS, during his remarkable career, he oversaw the creation and development of
22 multiple studios, including Turner Studios, Third Rail Studios, and Qingdao Oriental Movie
23 Industrial Park, culminating in his final role as president and general manager of studio
24 operations at Tyler Perry Studios; and
25 WHEREAS, he further served the film industry as a member of the Governor's Advisory
26 Committee on Film, Music & Digital Entertainment; chair of the Georgia Screen
27 Entertainment Coalition; board member of both ArtsNow Inc. and the Atlanta Jewish Film
28 Festival; and president of the Georgia Production Partnership; and
29 WHEREAS, he graduated with the 2020 Class of Leadership Atlanta, forging a strong and
30 lasting bond with his cohort members; and
31 WHEREAS, Steve Mensch actively participated in the lives of his children, Charles,
32 Adelayna, and Josephine, by encouraging their interests and volunteering at their schools in
33 Fayette County; and
